reviews.text: We absolutely loved our dinner. There was something for the picky kids, vegans, and carnivores in our group.

I’ve been coming here since I was a little kid and sadly it’s not as busy as it used to be, but the food is just as delicious as I remember. When I was young, I got a green tea milkshake every time and I’m happy to say it tastes just as amazing as always. Last week I went and had the japchae and kimchi trio while my friend got the bibambap loaded with steak, chicken, and eggs.  We were incredibly satisfied and felt our stuffed stomachs matched the homey feel just right. Will be back soon!

Mark's kitchen staff was very nice. The welcoming atmosphere brought me back. I had a good asparagus and shiitake mushroom omelette, and a nice cup of coffee. They have vegan and vegetarian options. Plus a nice mix of Korean flavors.

Fun cafe atmosphere, and seems like, if you're ordering breakfast/brunch, you're in luck. The place was hopping around lunch time and people looked happy. The salad I ordered sounded promising, but this was handily the weirdest salad I've ever gotten. My gluten free dining partner ordered the gluten free fried rice and found it inedible.
Great service. Steak and kimchi omlett was good 👍 reasonable prices

The food was delicious. They're doing curbside so make sure you order ahead. We're from Indiana so we were unaware.  The wait was very minimal and the people were very nice. The hot honey peppeoni piza was amazing! Definitely give it a shot. The crust was really good too thin but not like cracker thin, a little softer leaningtowardshand tossed. Kind of the best of both worlds. I could see myself eating here regularly if we lived near by. Also, the cheese fries, they're a lot, tons of bacon, tasty!

Consistency taste delicious, my family and I have ordered from here several times. Wow! Ledo's Pizza, Old Bay and Barbecue wings were fantastic; very fast and good customer service. Pizza was cheesy, saucy and well baked. My family enjoyed it, highly recommend, and will return. Compliments to the employees making the pizza it’s always delicious!

went to two spots (downtown silver spring/DC borderline on Georgia Ave and the one on International Drive) absolutely loved it! hospitality is superb, pizza was delicious, all the ingredients was fresh, salads also good, enough seating, it’s a nice change from your typical dominoes and pizza hut, I prefer Ledos to be honest.

Really good chicken wings, well cooked and flavorable. Korean BBQ sauce has enough spice to get warm feeling taste. Same for the siracha sauce (menu lists more than 7 or so).
Prices are reasonable considering the overall food. Friendly service, pretty fast even accounting for busy Saturday dinner time.

February 2022 update - only phone or online orders. But the food is good & friendly service.

You get what you pay for. I live 2 blocks away from this place and I finally decided to give them a shot and food is disappointing. Pizza “deluxe” was topped with way too much bacon, crispy chicken wings were burn chicken wings, place is dirty, carpet is filthy and windows looks like never been clean. I work in the restaurant industry so I know how this works.

This place is hit or miss depending on who is in the kitchen. I've had great food - especially pizza - but the rest of the menu frequently struggles to keep up. Caprese salad tomatoes were unremarkable at best and served with large basil leaves that are hard to cut into edible portions  with provided butter knife. Bean salad served underdressed with large chunks of red onion instead of minced or julienned giving the impression of eating beans from a can with sub sandwich toppings. A little more attention to detail and tasting the food could really improve the kitchen.  Service struggles as well.

Great little pizza shop and a beautiful historic strip of Takoma Park. Placed my order online and the pizza was ready and hot. Great dough, nice and soft. Had the ham pepperoni and sausage as a toppings. Perfect size to share. Highly recommended.

The food is absolutely amazing.  I had the fresh green beans with grape tomatoes.  The balsamic vinaigrette sauce was so flavorful.  The pizza was my main course again it was absolutely fabulous.  The atmosphere is so warm and inviting from the music to the staff.  I would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking to great food.

Long-standing fixture in Takoma Park...been to the place a few times over the years. Overall very good but it does have some unevenness. The doneness of the pizzas seems to vary a bit...mine was underdone, but the flavor is still very good, though. Service was friendlier than expected for a busy Sunday during a street festival. Our server took great care of us while balancing a busy service.

Fantastic pizzas with thin, wood-fired crush and generously yet appropriately apportioned amounts of perfectly matched toppings. Great appetizers. The naturally sweet fire-roasted beets go incredibly well with goat cheese natural sourness topping a fresh baguette. One of my favorite restaurants in the area.
This store has made so many mistakes with my order is so simple to even make a non meat sandwich one of the staff is so rude. They need to retrain staff

Decent Subway outlet serving Subway's standardised menu of choice, including subway sandwiches, sandwich meats, fixings, condiments, and soft drinks. the location has some space outside to afford outdoor eating if the weather appeals. Subway is a take it or leave it place - you know what you are getting, the only question is whether the standard meets the franchise's aspiration. in this case, the answer is yes.

Messed up my entire order. Wouldn’t remake the order, refund me or do anything.

They don’t honor curbside, it’s dangerous to pull up directly to the store where it’s located so there’s a subway parking lot on the side where curbside was done before so I pulled inside and waited. Never came. I had to call 4 times and finally a woman with an angry tone came outside after I had to pull in front of the store which is literally a main road with no way to pull over, she almost threw my food in my car.

This subway is horrible. Don’t give them your money.

Edit: This isn’t the first or second time they’ve messed my order so I hadn’t been back in awhile but others have complained about this store and I’ll be filing a complaint with the proper agency to investigate this location. It is unethical to not provide a refund or make the order right. The employee outright admitted to messing the order up and wouldn’t do anything. If the General Manager would like to reach out to me, you can respond with your number or email, thanks.

Ayo, the chicken doesn’t taste good, it’s as if the inner meat is raw, if I get food poisoning, I’ll update you all.

-update; yes, so I did get food poisoning, it isn’t that bad, a lot of bathroom trips and I did vomit three times.

Was an ok experience. The lunch time gets very busy, we had to wait for a long time. I ask for the chicken ginger wrap was very tasty. My friend loved hers too. It’s a very small place with very few tables. Parking lot in the back with small spaces but good enough for DC.
I had little to no contact with the staff but they sound polite enough.
Went for lunch with a friend and was pleasantly surprised. The town area is great and then the food was exactly how I like it. Portion size and price was great and would definitely come back.

A local Takoma Park institution, Olive Lounge serves up some fantastic pub fare with some very surprisingly tasty vegetarian and non vegetarian options.  They have a nice selection of beers, and plenty of space.  The back bar is a really nice spot to hang out and kick back with some friends.

Ordered take out from here tonight. Wonderful. Delicious. Well-priced and delicious. The salads were fresh with decent portions.  The entrees were excellent. I am thinking about coming back tomorrow to have it again. This will definitely become one of my regular hangouts.
Absolutely love this place!  My favorite part is the service they are so nice and welcoming 🙏 oh and the deserts are amazing!

Love this place. The food is bomb the atmosphere is wonderful and friendly and very important to me; my vegetarian wife loves the menu and has really well thought out choices. The specials are always on point
Good service, friendly staff. A community favorite. Call your order in, they are busy. The sit down eating area is closed

GREAT FOOD.  FRIENDLY STAFF  ORDERED FRIED FISH.. FRIES. & COLE SLAW & POTATOES. VERY TASTY.  FISH NOT AS GOOD AS IT USE TO BE…FISH WAS A LITTLE TO SOFT, EVEN WHEN I ASKED FOR MY FISH TO BE FRIED HARD. . OVERALL,   A GREAT PLACE TO EAT.
Love this place but the hours suck. The portion sizes are smaller and more expensive than what it use to be. But the fish sandwiches are still delicious!!

I received near burned chicken and hush puppies along with tasteless crab fries. The food was not what I was use to from the historic former DC hit chicken and fish place. It was that same as the Chinese restaurant food. Greasy with a puddle of oil in the bottom of the plastic containers. They didn’t even punch holes to make sure the fish and chicken didn’t sweat. I found out that they are a franchise operation now, so beware of where you order, if you order bc, in my opinion Horace and Dickies no longer exists. The taste, the quality is gone. I called to let the Glenarden store know what my order looked like. No apology, the guy just said we will try to do better. That is not acceptable! How about changing you old oil so food comes out the right color and flavor! It’s sad to see Horace and Dickies go out like this! Very very disappointed ☹️ in the food. 2 stars are for the sides.

I've Been Coming Here Since I Was A child , This Isnt The H&D That I Grew Up On . The Service Was Good But the Food Was Beyond Nasty . NO FLAVOR TO ANYTHING! The Hush Puppies Were Like Bricks. the Yams Were Watery , The Mac N Cheese Had NO FLAVOR . The Fish Had No Seasoning . The Hot Sauce Ain't Even Have No Flavor . I Gave Them A 1 Star Cause I Had To Not Cause They Deserve It .

Peaches was very good. I would recommend this place is you are looking for Jamaican and soul food in the DC area.
3 stars because of a few things that are near and dear to me personally. But some people may not care. Everything was seasoned and flavored perfectly. If you don’t like spicy curry, stay away 😂. My curry shrimp was spicy.

Oxtails- 7- I like mine to fall off the bone. I had to
Work on these a little. But great savory flavor.
Fried whitening-7- I would have given a ten. But these were not whole filets. They were broken. The sauce that was provided was a 10! 🤤🤤.
Curry Shrimp- 10
Greens-10
Rice-5 it was cold &
Mild Flavor( but the curry sauce made up for it.
Green beans- 10 so good!!!!
Plantains-10
Garlic Mashed potatoes-10

It was my first time ordering from Peaches but not my last.  I was pleased with the entire process from ordering to pick up.

The food is flavorful and plenty for two servings per meal.  My sister loved her oxtails, lay some sugar sweet potatoes and cabbage.

I enjoyed the stuffed salmon with crab and shrimp, cabbage and mac and cheese.

The meals do not come with plantains as I am accustomed to having so be sure to place an order as a side if you want them.  They were cooked to perfection and there's plenty in the order to share.

Overall very pleased.

The Customer  Service was phenomenal
Especially Phillip, the gentleman that greeted us at the door. He assisted us and explained every detail of the menu.

I didn't get the young lady her name. She was short and wore eyeglasses

She was phenomenal as well, Smiling and organized with assisting the other workers in the Kitchen.

I tried several meals and I was very impressed with the Turkey meatloaf; and Macaroni and Cheese were so delicious.
I will return again

Thank You for the Great Customer Service

My family and  I ate here the Friday after Christmas. We each ordered different dishes to eat family style. My favorites were the curry shrimp, oxtail, and spinach and cheese patty- pie. My favorites and the other dishes were absolutely delicious!  We will be back. Thank you for the great service and generous portions. Sandi & Family

The restaurant is nice and clean. The young guy working their is extremely helpful. The food is given to you nice and hot. However, I didn't care to much for the food. The best thing was the beef patti, the fried whiting is mediocre, the collards were not good, and the green beans were tolerable. The service was great.

HORRIBLE customer service and plain flavorless food.

Went in there with my friends a couple times and they were rude. We let it slide because we were hungry and that was the only pizza place open around. Went in there today for the third time and they were being extremely rude AGAIN.

We were just asking him simple questions respectfully and he kept telling us to shut up.
We put up with it for a couple minutes, but then he got really nasty and we just decided to leave instead.

Pick one struggle man. Can’t have a bad attitude and bad food. Pick one!

don’t even try to hide how racist they are. So difficult to talk to , will ignore your questions and tell you not to worry when you ask for the total. 0 stars. Terrible customer service especially towards POC customers.

Coworker got 5 wings and drink for $7.45. They were likely made weeks ago or left out too long: slimy, soft, and inedible. I feel a little sick after simply licking the grease off of my finger. I was too horrified to even take a bite

If I could give this place a negative zero stars I would. First of all they are scammers. Their medium sized is actually a small pizza. Their large is actually a medium-sized pizza and their extra large is actually a large sized pizza. The man in there is very disrespectful and talks to you as if he's back in his country. You can tell he has no respect for women. I paid for medium pizza but got a small. I will never ever order there again. Do not go there.

I have to admit that I've lived in Takoma Park for a long time and I've always avoided pizza movers. The reviews online made it sound like there were better places to go, and we always went to Roscoe's or Timber for our high end pizzas, and Domino's for our quick and easy pizzas.  We got pizza from Pizza Movers for the first time ever recently and really enjoyed it. No customer service issues of any sort, which we were bracing for based on the reviews. We have since had PM a couple more times, and the only issue that we have seen is that the flavor has been a little inconsistent, but it's still really good. Cheese is a B+, toppings are a B+, sauce is an A, and crust is a solid  B.  We are going to continue to go here for as long as they serve us decent pizza - and for as long as we don't run into any customer service issues.

Does this look like extra cheese? This was one of the driest pizzas I’ve ever had from Domino’s. The quality has deteriorated. I literally threw the Domino’s Pizza away and ordered from Papa Johns. Domino’s is the picture to the left while Papa Johns is the picture to the right. Clearly a huge difference. I’ve officially given up on Domino’s. Too many bad experiences.

I order xl pizza and get this pizza come on i working in pizza place’s more then 10 years and this one is not pizza and asked they said can’t make it better because this xtra large I not give any recommendations this place I waste my money

My pizza was delivered 1 hr and 15 min after it came out the oven.   The driver said they were waiting for the wings.   We all know that's a lie because the wings are never cooked well.  Someone else in my group wanted them.   I complained online, received a confirmation# and nothing else.   The next time I attempted to order trough the app, online, by phone and directly to the store I was told they could no longer deliver to my house.   Since they have been delivering for the past 3 years, I can only conclude that it's now because I made a complaint!   When I asked the manager, I wasn't given any explanation.  Do yourself a favor a go somewhere else!  I know we did and will from now on!

Domino's location 4362 (6239 Georgia Ave NW, Washington, DC 20011) has the most awful customer service. I called in a large pan pizza for pick-up and was routed to Domino's call center. When I arrived at the restaurant, I paid for the pizza in full, but was then presented with a thin-crust pizza. I asked the cashier (who also claimed to be the manager) if he could redo my order. He replied "if you pay for it." I offered to pay the difference between the pan and thin crust, but he insisted that I pay for a whole new pizza. When I asked for a refund of the first order that they got wrong, he refused.

After explaining my frustration over the matter, he refused service: "how about I just refund you your money and you won't get a pizza." When I asked for a refund receipt, he said "we don't do that."

The manager was so rude and disrespectful. He also didn't seem knowledgable about the company or know how to do his job. He claimed that Domino's doesn't have a call center that takes orders; that only the store takes orders. His pants were also hanging below his waistline, making me question the cleanliness of this location. I'll never order food from here again.

This Domino's has the worst customer service experience.  I went to complain about an issue with my delivery and the manager/parter of the franchise came out to speak to me. Right he was defensive and dismissive without  even expressing one word of empathy.  In the end telling me to get out and that he was calling the police because I said I was going to write a negative review about his place  on Google...I live in neighborhood and I advise all my neighbors to go somewhere else for there pizza!

Amazing vegan food that changes from day to day. Everything is very flavorful and well seasoned. We always get the wings with taste really close to real chicken and alway hit. The greens are always tender, and the vegan mac is something special. It's hard to make good cheese substitute but they nail it. Always friendly staff to chat with. Really good vegan deserts as well. We come back every few months.

The most tasty vegan food. The food is good, the service is good. The menu items are a little pricey. I have tried nice popular vegan spots in the city such as: Equinox restaurant which is pricey and has some yummy options, Nu Vegan, as well as Farewell, and Sticky fingers … the list goes on and on but have not tried a place that tops Elife yet!

Very bad tasting food. Ordered two entrees and a side. Something just smells and tastes wrong about everything. There's definitely far, far better vegan food available at other places. I rarely write negative reviews but this food is just too terrible to ignore quietly. Had to throw about 2/3rds of my order into the trash after I couldn't tolerate it anymore and bought a drink from next door to get rid of the food's taste. Total waste of $17. Give this place a miss, and you won't miss anything.

Waste of money. I ordered Eggplant Parmesan with kale and cashew macaroni and cheese. Everything tasted burnt and old. I'm still not sure if the eggplant was eggplant. I remember when Everlasting Life was stellar. The food tasted like life. Elife is a disappointing mess now. The food tasted like death.
Delicious, tasty, well seasoned comfort food, 100% vegan, great customer service. Moderate prices, satisfying portions.

11/23/2022 4:16pm. I used Starbucks mobile to order my drinks. I was coming from a walk with my sister and two dogs, our plan was to sit in the patio once I pick up the drinks because the sun was still out and weather was warm. I noticed that there weren’t any seats at the patio? So I asked one of the employees if I can take one seat from inside (since it was clearly all stacked up) and bring it outside AND that I will put it back. The employee (didn’t catch his name) but he was wearing white headphones was giving me an attitude telling me “no we can’t do that. You can’t do that” and I told him “well dogs aren’t allowed in Starbucks, but they are allowed outside and I want to sit outside with my dogs, but there aren’t any chairs at the patio. And then he was like “yeah fine whatever. Take the chair” like… sir, I’m sorry that requesting a chair for an empty patio brings you so much trouble… Drinks were great, but that employee specifically could’ve been respectful. He was doing too much for a chair. If he was required to clear the patio at a certain time, then that would make sense. But he didn’t say anything and was just flat out rude.

Update: Just tell your workers and that particular worker that I described to you on that DAY to be respectful and not give an attitude for asking a SIMPLE question. It doesn’t cost anything to be respectful.

** TERRIBLE PARKING!! **

The baristas work fast and the food is prepared as ordered.

But the parking is atrocious ! Four  businesses share 10 spots, including a barbershop.  If you arrive before 8:00 a.m., you can find a spot but after 5:00p.m.?  Forget it. You get overflow parking by Busboys and Poets patrons.

No where to park. With very little parking. Not busy, just 1 person in front of me when I went.

When it was my turn, the gentlemen never said anything,, but turned and walked away. Never coming back, a young lady took my order.

Simple order or 2 tall Caremel Brule frapps. She made hot coffee, and got a attitude when I told her they where frapps.

Sarcastically apologized, saying it's really busy in here. Remind you, not busy, bearly any online orders.

Very friendly, helpful staff and great service here.

In general, Starbucks drinks are overpriced for the quality/flavor.

The worse customer service ever. There were just two employees working. One making the drinks another taking orders. I placed a mobile order for a TRENTA sized pumpkin cold brew with two shots. It was my free one which is why I made it big. I arrive about 30 min after I submitted order and it wasn’t on counter but I seen them making drinks for people just walking in so I ask lady with blonde hair at register. She said I don’t know. And she told me to look again. I did amc asked her if she could just remake it bc somebody prob stole it. I wait another 10 min and she brings the coffee and says “ I made it a venti since I had the wait. I said I didn’t order venti I ordered TRENTA . She just looked at me so with mad face so I said never mind and walked out. She didn’t put the two shots I ordered with the coffee in it and it taste terrible. I will not be going back to this one ever again. I had another thing happened when they were giving out free cups . I ordered pumpkin and thought that would be considered holiday drink but it wasn’t. When I asked the lady who was working the counter about the free cup she said pumpkin not considered holiday drink so k asked which ones were so I could just place order bc I wanted to get that free cup for someone. She looked at me as if I was the biggest pain in her you know what for even asking this and handed me the cup anyways but the entire time she looked like she wanted to strangle me. I’m from Cleveland ( the land of rudeness ) but the Starbucks employees are AMAZING in Cleveland. In DC they need some major personality changes. If you hate CS jobs get another one. Here is a pic of my pumpkin cream cold brew with the foam. This is NOT what it normally is.

It is Thai and sushi restaurant. They are 5 dine in tables and outdoor seating. But now there is no table service for outdoor. You can place an order online or at the counter. Once the food is ready, they will bring it out for you. The food will be served in the Togo containers though.

Yum yum yum. I found this little gem today and decided to give it a try. They didn’t disappoint. The food was so flavorful. I was able to add vegetables, broccoli and substitute with brown rice. I will definitely be returning for another healthier version of fried rice.

These positive reviews are hard to believe given our experience tonight. Our order didn't taste or look like Thai food, but instead something a home cook might throw together. My pineapple fried rice included what looked like canned pineapples. It also had green beans, broccoli, and cabbage, none of which belong in that dish. My partner got pad thai noodles that came with brussel sprouts! Pretty ridiculous. The noodles also tasted like they included ketchup. This was all pretty disappointing. There are much better, authentic Thai places just up the road in Silver Spring.

Everything was prepared with delicious detail - crispy cashew chicken had a refreshingly veggie-forward medley of green onions, bell peppers, and added broccoli. Everything was crunchy and so perfect texture-wise. I've never given the California Roll the time of day, but they use tuna instead of crab lies. Refreshing and satisfying. Good quality tuna. The red curry was smooth and spicy, and the brown rice was wild and beautiful. Spectacular dinner!

We had items missing from our order and some of the food was too spicy to eat despite being marked 1 or 2 stars (out of 5). It was also very dry, the pad se ew had a lot of dry noodles stuck together. I like to support local restaurants and wish I could give a higher review but after waiting a long time for the food it was quite disappointing.

Outstanding. Random visit as we wanted to try something new and this was perfect. Small shop and I felt the love. Chicken quesadilla + the spicy sauce was good! So much meat. But the dessert was the all star here. Absolute heaven and I would drive 1,000 miles for it.

Great vegan/vegetarian options as well.

live nearby but hadn’t been until now due to sticker shock when reviewing their menu. got a gift certificate for christmas and tried it out; food was delicious and servings were large. great vibe in the restaurant as well with cool art and plants. we split the kfc sandwich and it was very tasty but at $16 it was quite the splurge (no sides included). our bibimbap ($19 each) was good and more food than expected. online menu was too extensive and it took a while to scroll through on my phone and decide. enjoyed the meal but not sure when we will return soon due to the over $30 cost per person without any drinks.

4.5 stars…..Wow the food here is SO good! The food takes a long time, so don’t expect this to be a quick in and out - but it’s so worth it.  They have delish chicken dishes if you’re bringing a non-vegan.

It was sooooo good. And it was such a busy night they ran out of food but still remained oh so professional and so kind when people kept coming in.  Clearly this is THE place to be. And to add, everyone who was turned away were so cool about it. I would go back. PG county girl...

This is a small place in a local Neighborhood. The staff were very friendly. There is paid parking on the street. The food tasted very good. The menu is very diverse with lot of veggie and meat options. The portions are filling. Cauliflower Japche was amazing. It’s a must try. Over all it’s a great place.
I wanted to make some Ethiopian dishes, so I needed some essential ingredients. They were very nice and helped me find everything on my list, will go back again.

I had a takeout few times. Food is very good even though it's little bit pricy. You get what you paid. If you eat inside few things there is no cold drink even water and soda. Machine is been broken for a while so does the toilet . It makes loud sound when it fills up the tank. Bathroom needs total renovation.

The spices aren't labeled clearly to show what you're getting. I had to go off what I thought it was and will have to taste. The lady behind the counter was super nice. I should have asked her which were which. The other customers seemed a bit rude to me though, but not the staff.
A must see and visit if your in Addis. Expect find dining beautiful Gallery and much more
They have very good Ethiopian items including powerful Arake or katikala

Edit 11/05/22: dine in is now open!

Customer service is nice most of the time. I like the employees here they do their best. The food sometimes doesn’t come as you ordered or they forget some stuff, which is a major inconvenience.

This location supports mobile order pick up now, which is great - only negative thing is you cannot order Taco Bell through the app.

The new interior is pretty clean, they’ve changed it drastically as compared to before the pandemic hit.

It's a dead, restaurant with barking service members who'd rather talk to you as though you've done wrong by just coming in. The food is awful and the African guy is very rude. I think he owns it. I saw him be rude to a delivery guy for just picking up food. I'm sure he'll write about his experience too. I cannot belive this place has returning customers but hey its the only kfc around.. guess it's Popeyes from now on. They were rude to almost everyone I saw and the food looked old.

This specific location always have issues….rude people that work there and they close earlier than the time posted. I went at 10:15pm and they said they were closed, when the sign posted said they closed at 11pm.
Ordered online 10 min before I arrived so I could pick it up and leave when I arrived. When I arrived, I had to wait an extra 10 min for the two wraps I ordered.
Despite a $60 plus dollar order they left out of delivery Mac and cheese for my granddaughter. They simply don’t care or are totally incompetent. When we called no one answered. Don’t use this kfc

Best Trinidadian food in the area! Portion size is great and the menu is just delicious! We had the curry goat, curry shrimp, bake and shark, doubles, bussup shut and the natural passion fruit juices! Highly reccomend this places especially for a quick and go bite!
First time trying Trinidad food and it was good. Don’t have much to compare it to but it seemed all right to me. The server was nice and I like the flavor of the chicken roti.
Ordered a huge and delicious chicken roti at a cheap price, as well as some doubles. The roti was top notch, and the doubles were good. Super friendly owner, definitely recommend stopping here.
Doubles were drier than the Sahara desert; NOT fresh; chick peas--NOT SEASONED; bland bland. Skins were heated via microwave,  which made it TOUGH to eat.

Had to wait 30 mins for my order. 1 buss up shot is $16. That is MADNESS. The curry had no taste, no flavor. The curry mango was not good. The buss up shot skin was hard and damn near burnt. I drove from southern Va just for this and was HIGHLY DISAPPOINTED.

Empanada were ok. They were large but didn’t really have flavor . And idk if it was a bad day or just their style of making it but my Jamaican and Chorizo empanadas were really dry.  The cashier was nice though.

The Jamaican beef empanada was tasteless.
The chicken salteña was flavorful.
The cashier was rude. We started eating the empanadas at the store and he asked us to not eat in the store as they have rodent issues. 😨
Fantastic empanadas and salteñas! Big portions, and stuffing selection of flavors is really good.

Delicious!!! I got a variety today and each empanada was better than the next. The peach guava and Jamaican were my favorite so far. All staff were wearing masks and gloves. Can't wait to come back for more!
Julia’s is delicious.  They are also now OPEN ON WEEKENDS!
Been coming here for years I’m very disappointed. Was given old chicken. I only gave 4 stars because normally their food is never a miss but this definitely disappointed me.
For $8 -$10 for a meal the portions are generous and the service is good.

Cheap overpriced food I can’t imagine I paid 10& for this. This is supposed to be a chicken rice noodle but there were just some few strips of chicken fat and hardly any vegetables. The food was tasteless so I kept adding soy sauce.

The food is good. Better than the average little sub shop. What makes it great is the service, the "at home" feel they give. They remember you, remember your favorites, those little request...it kinda surprising. When I come to DC area to visit,  I will make it a point to go back!

We have been ordering from Peter's Sub for about 5years now. On June 2, my daughter's birthday, the food we ordered was horrible. We were given very old severally refried chicken, old beef lo mein   this old steak sandwich was given instead of 2 order of spring rolls - my daughter had stomach pains plus diarrhea after eating. Too bad!!! Please go back to your good times.

We absolutely loved the food and service. Our waitress, Kelly, was amazing. She was very knowledgeable on the menu and gave us great suggestions on what to order. The drinks were delicious. Very friendly staff and very clean.

Unfortunately we went there when they were ready to close. Didn't have the opportunity to taste. But the vibe was there just when you get out the elevator, you feel it.
